R: Read — Reads user input.
E: Evaluate — Executes the code.
P: Print — Outputs the result.
L: Loop — Waits for the next input.

How to use Node.js REPL: Open terminal enter "node"

> 2 + 3
5

> const greet = (name) => `Hello, ${name}`;
undefined

> greet('Mahesh')
'Hello, Mahesh' // output

.exit : Exit the REPL
